timeline.bodyText:
Please, don't create a new instance of LevenshteinDistance for each search.
We have 3 possible distance values (0, 1 and 2). So, just create 3 constants of LevenshteinDistance and reuse them.
I.e.
private static final LevenshteinDistance ZERO_LEVENSHTEIN_DISTANCE = new LevenshteinDistance(0);
private static final LevenshteinDistance ONE_LEVENSHTEIN_DISTANCE = new LevenshteinDistance(1);
private static final LevenshteinDistance TWO_LEVENSHTEIN_DISTANCE = new LevenshteinDistance(2);

After that we can rewrite the method to be as following:
private static boolean isFuzzy(String term, String value){
    term = term.trim();
    if (term.length() < 3) {
        return ZERO_LEVENSHTEIN_DISTANCE.apply(value, term) == 0;
    } else if (term.length() < 6) {
        int levenshteinDist = ONE_LEVENSHTEIN_DISTANCE.apply(value, term);
        return levenshteinDist <= 1 && levenshteinDist >= 0;
    }
    int levenshteinDist = TWO_LEVENSHTEIN_DISTANCE.apply(value, term);
    return levenshteinDist <= 2 && levenshteinDist >= 0;
}

